♪To set sail for distant seas♪

5
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:29,120
♪Rumors swirl close to my ears♪

6
00:00:29,120 --> 00:00:31,650
♪Some laugh and say my dreams are wild♪

7
00:00:31,650 --> 00:00:34,900
♪Yet I will not change
my original aspiration♪

8
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:36,900
♪Even if it means running into a wall♪

9
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,150
♪I know the road
to growing up brings pain♪

10
00:00:39,410 --> 00:00:41,880
♪Still, I hold fast
to the dream I cherish♪

11
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:44,490
♪Never have I thought to yield♪

12
00:00:44,490 --> 00:00:46,720
♪Youth is meant
to stand against the world♪

13
00:00:47,030 --> 00:00:47,990
♪I've always longed♪

14
00:00:47,990 --> 00:00:49,580
♪To stand upon the highest peak♪

15
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:50,570
♪I've always wished♪

16
00:00:50,570 --> 00:00:52,180
♪To cross a river wide and deep♪

17
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:55,800
♪In darkness,
look up to see the sky turn clear♪

18
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,240
♪Unyielding♪

19
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:59,780
♪The butterfly reborn
from its cocoon must fly♪

20
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:03,320
♪Like bamboo breaking forth,
I chase dreams through hardship♪

21
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:06,190
♪Return to me, my dream♪

22
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:07,430
♪Unyielding♪

23
00:01:07,430 --> 00:01:09,980
♪My pure heart stays the same♪

24
00:01:09,980 --> 00:01:10,980
♪You must face the wind♪

25
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:13,520
♪And go where your heart leads♪

26
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,560
♪Embrace the moonlight
that belongs to you♪

27
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,040
♪In the dark♪

28
00:01:18,060 --> 00:01:21,500
=Voyage to Haihun, Season 1=

29
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:23,220
=Episode 9=

30
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:29,120
Hey.

31
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:30,640
Two things. First...

32
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,480
De Jiu is gone.

33
00:01:31,490 --> 00:01:32,330
What?

34
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,640
She and Master tricked me
out of tuition,

35
00:01:34,660 --> 00:01:36,230
then held me hostage, and just left?

36
00:01:36,230 --> 00:01:37,740
Don't you want to be a wandering hero?

37
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:39,570
- You...
- Wandering heroes are like this.

38
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:41,960
Second thing,

39
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:43,680
Lord Gong says there will be an exam?

40
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:44,710
Duke, don't worry.

41
00:01:45,150 --> 00:01:46,330
- The exam
- The exam?

42
00:01:46,330 --> 00:01:48,040
is just a show
for the people of Chang'an.

43
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:52,590
Besides, every man here is gifted.

44
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:55,400
Shouldn't we let
the people of Chang'an see that?

45
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,280
Gifted.

46
00:01:56,630 --> 00:01:57,790
An exam is enough to prove it?

47
00:01:57,790 --> 00:01:58,680
Of course.

48
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,560
Aren't I the examiner?

49
00:02:01,950 --> 00:02:02,920
When the time comes,

50
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,590
I'll set the questions nice and easy.

51
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:06,850
The scores would naturally soar.

52
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,360
The fairness of the exam

53
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,280
is just to silence the court.

54
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:12,450
You understand?

55
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,830
Yes.

56
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:16,820
I'll go prepare the questions.

57
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:18,150
Wait for my word.

58
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:19,270
Thanks.

59
00:02:20,710 --> 00:02:21,550
Duke.

60
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,800
How's it going?

61
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:23,940
No need to ask that.

62
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,520
Wang Heng is the examiner.

63
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,890
How could there be any problem?

64
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:28,280
I've taken care of everything.

65
00:02:29,260 --> 00:02:30,630
Oh.

66
00:02:36,020 --> 00:02:38,140
(Longshan Inn, Examination Area)

67
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:39,120
Mathematics problems.

68
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,430
A cage holds both chickens and rabbits.

69
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:42,560
Look up,

70
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:43,680
and you see 35 heads.

71
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:45,280
Look down,

72
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,710
and you see 94 feet.

73
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:47,920
How many chickens

74
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:50,000
and how many rabbits are there?

75
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,870
These fowl and livestock
do reflect daily life,

76
00:02:57,630 --> 00:02:59,820
but such rustic puzzles

77
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:02,270
hardly match the grand strategies
of the realm.

78
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:04,590
Logic problems.

79
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,750
There are four officials:
A, B, C, and D.

80
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:08,910
Each comes from a different county.

81
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:11,240
Here are four statements about them.

82
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:12,630
Only two of them are true.

83
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,410
First,

84
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:16,400
A comes from County A
and performs excellently.

85
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:17,350
Second,

86
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,030
if B is from County B,

87
00:03:19,030 --> 00:03:20,190
then he has made a mistake.

88
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:21,190
Third,

89
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,180
C has made no mistake

90
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:23,270
and is not from County C.

91
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:25,190
Fourth, D is from County D

92
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:26,310
and performs the worst.

93
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:28,190
So, among these four statements,

94
00:03:28,190 --> 00:03:29,750
which two are correct?

95
00:03:31,090 --> 00:03:32,830
Lord Wang, please, stop.

96
00:03:33,130 --> 00:03:34,630
I'm all muddled now.

97
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:39,080
Though an official must always discern
right from wrong,

98
00:03:39,370 --> 00:03:40,840
this puzzle...

99
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,870
I understand.

100
00:03:41,870 --> 00:03:44,530
Logic questions don't concern the realm.

101
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:46,320
Alright, fine.

102
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:47,710
Let me handle it instead.

103
00:03:47,840 --> 00:03:48,910
Much obliged to you.

104
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:50,580
Why can't I go in?

105
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,200
Ignore him; keep writing.

106
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,120
Forgive me, Duke.

107
00:03:55,210 --> 00:03:56,520
Lord Wang has given instructions.

108
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,750
This exam concerns
the selection of talents.

109
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,430
It must be treated with utmost secrecy.

110
00:04:00,430 --> 00:04:01,680
So, when setting the questions,

111
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,780
the one drafting them
must be kept in isolation.

112
00:04:03,790 --> 00:04:05,270
No contact with outsiders is allowed.

113
00:04:05,270 --> 00:04:06,120
That won't do.

114
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,080
I must see Wang Heng.

115
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,710
Wang Heng, I know you're inside.

116
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:13,400
You shameless rascal.

117
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,200
Take it back.

118
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:50,680
Lord Wang.

119
00:04:50,820 --> 00:04:52,360
The exam papers are ready.

120
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:54,270
Very well, thanks, Lord Gong.

121
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:08,940
(Longshan Inn)

122
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:30,300
(Examination Paper Seal)

123
